        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued June 16 at 4:17PM MDT by NWS Denver CO</headline>
        <description>At 417 PM MDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm near
Purcell, or 20 miles north of Greeley, moving east at 40 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 40 mph and half inch size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor damage to outdoor objects is possible.

Locations impacted include...
Pierce, Purcell, Briggsdale and Cornish.
</description>
        <instruction>Monitor the weather situation closely and be alert for threatening
weather conditions.</instruction>
